			<ns0:name>mli...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/109474787648168037085/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">&lt;b&gt;[Please summarize the enhancement so it will be comprehensible to someone&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;from outside the Native Client team. A good summary will include:]&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;b&gt;- Where are we today?&lt;/b&gt;
Currently, there are two version of this code that cause confusion and process breakage.  One is in native_client.  The other, dangerous one is in the ian_rsp branch of the vsx project.
[e.g. &amp;quot;Currently each platform uses a different address space size.&amp;quot;]

&lt;b&gt;- Why is this a problem?&lt;/b&gt;
Because it makes it really hard to plan work that depends on this code.
[e.g. &amp;quot;This can make portability complicated.&amp;quot;]

&lt;b&gt;- The proposed enhancement:&lt;/b&gt;
Create a canonical version of this code that is versioned by one and only one system, namely the native_client's version control.
[e.g. &amp;quot;All platforms should move to 1GB untrusted space.&amp;quot;]

&lt;b&gt;- Exit criteria:&lt;/b&gt;
We're done when it has passed code review and the other version has been deleted.
&lt;b&gt;[How do we know we're done?]&lt;/b&gt;

&lt;b&gt;- Anticipated impact:&lt;/b&gt;
&lt;b&gt;[for users as well as other parts of the system]&lt;/b&gt;
low, since this code in native_client is only compiled by developers when they plan on using it.  This will be addressed in future issues.
